  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House", 
    "date": "2016-09-26T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "This bill amends the Safe Drinking Water Act to authorize states and the Environmental Protection Agency to require public water systems that have repeatedly failed to comply with drinking water standards to assess options for consolidation.\n\nPublic water systems are eligible for financial assistance to assist with undertaking consolidation activities.\n\nAdditionally, the bill provides liability protection for compliant public water systems that consolidate with non-compliant systems."
